  "texts": [
    "But the board of directors also needs to take risks seriously and be willing to do something about them.",
    "This will often require a good relationship between the ethics board and the board of directors.",
    "Inversely, it would be harder for the ethics board to reduce risk if the board of directors mainly cares about other things (e.g., profits or prestige), especially since the ethics board is usually not able to force the board of directors to do something.",
    "Overseeing the development and deployment processThe ethics board could also be responsible for overseeing the development and deployment process.",
    "For example, Google DeepMind's Responsibility and Safety Council (RSC) makes recommendations about \"whether to proceed with the further development or deployment of a model, and/or about the safety and ethics stipulations under which a project should continue\" [63]."
  ],
